# Event Subscriptions

For event subscriptions, unsubscribe directly in the `Dispose` method. Do not use `DisposableToken` or add unsubscribe callbacks to `CompositeDisposable`.

## Pattern

```csharp
// ❌ BAD - using disposable token for unsubscribe
public void Initialize()
{
    _registry.SomeEvent += OnSomeEvent;
    _subscriptions.Add(new DisposableToken(() => _registry.SomeEvent -= OnSomeEvent));
}

public void Dispose()
{
    _subscriptions.Dispose();
}
```

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD - unsubscribe in Dispose
public void Initialize()
{
    _registry.SomeEvent += OnSomeEvent;
}

public void Dispose()
{
    _registry.SomeEvent -= OnSomeEvent;
}
```

## Rationale

- Unsubscribe logic is colocated with the class lifecycle
- No extra indirection or tokens
- Clearer ownership: Dispose is the single place for cleanup
